column2: Lake is much more clear than it has been since August.  Air temp is 60 degrees F- east-southeast since- ripple on water- increasing clouds since sunrise.
58 degrees F- partly sunny- high cirrus- strong SW wind- most leaves are down.
No leaves yet.  Air 54 degrees F.  Wind 10-20 mph from the east. clear.  Water 53 degrees F at 3 feet- choppy.  Rain 5/18-5/22 = .75".
76 degrees.  Gorgeous.  60 degree water temperature at surface.  Winds at 5-10 mph from the northwest.  Best day so far this year.  Rain 5/29 - 0.45 inches.
Popular cotton and pine pollen in top 1" along west shore.  1.75" of rain on 6/5/97.  Lake level up a little.  Surface temp back down to 63 degrees F.
West wind at 15-20 mph.  Light to moderate chop.  78 degrees F.  Few cumulus clouds.  Great day- wild iris in bloom.  Rain gauge reading from 5/18 to 6/22 = 3.45 inches.
Great day - 78 degrees F.  Winds southerly.  Ripple on the water.  High cirrus clouds - sun shimmering through.
Calm- few clouds. 40 degrees F last night.  Rain and cool weather have lowered lake temps form 72 degrees to 68 degrees F today.
Wind south-southeast 5-10 mph.  Mostly sunny- cumulus / cirrus clouds.
77 degrees.  Partly cloudy.  Cumulus clouds- dry - 0.1 inch rain last two weeks.  On July 27- 1997- lake was up 5 inches from lake mapping #989 from 7/20/97.

First frost 8/18.  Rainy and cloudy weather kept from taking samples and Secchi disk readings.  74 degrees F.  Mostly cloudy- wind from the south at 10-15 mph.  Cirrus and cumulus clouds.  Rain gauge from 7/16/97 to 9/1/97=5.28 in.
Lake starting to turn over.  64 degrees F from the surface to 12 feet.

The temperature is 70 degrees F.  Rain gauge reading from 9/1 to 10/05  = 4.45 inches.  Clear- south-southwest wind at 15-20 mph- gusting to 30 mph.  Early maple leaves down.  Birches golden.  Fish again suspended at 17 feet with turnover.
Ice out April 7th at 3 in the evening.  North-northeast winds at 10-15 mph.  65 degrees F. 95% clear.  Cirrus clouds.
65 degrees F- NE 15-20 mph white caps.  Water down 2 inches.  Very dry.
.35 " 5/4. 65 degrees F. WNW 0-5 mph.  Down 4.75 inches.
.35 "  5/11 -5/29.  1.6 inches 5/30 and 5/31.  Lake up still low.  NNW at 10-15 mph.  Frost tonight.
1 inch 6/1-4.  Cold with frost.  52 degrees.  Wind NNW 10-20 mph.  Lake near normal.
Lake level back up.  SE 0-5 mph.  68 degrees.  70% clear.
76 degrees F. Scattered cumulus west-southwest at 10-15 mph.  Lake 1 inch above normal.
1.3 inches 6/24-25.  ENE at 0-5 mph.  Cumulus 35%. 76 degrees F.
0.45 inches 6/27.  0.5 inches 6/30.  ENE at 0-5 mph.  Cumulus 20%.  70 degrees F.  3 fishing 1 tubing 1 rafting 12 P.O.
No wind no clouds 65 degrees F.  The temperature is 73 degrees F.  No rain 7/7-7/29.  0.25" 7/30.  Small bass and perch in shallows.
15-20 mph southwest.  65 degrees F.  73 degrees F at end of pier.  1 inch 8/16 0.6 8/22.
15-20 mph SW.  65 degrees F.  73 degrees F at end of pier.  1 inch 8/16 0.6 8/22.
15-20 mph from S variable.  80 degrees F.  72 degrees F at end of pier.  No clouds no rain.
No wind- 73 degrees F. 73 degrees F at end of pier. 50% cumulus cirrus.  No rain.  Color.
0-5 mph SSE.  77 degrees F. 70 degrees Fend of pier.  20% cumulus.  High haze 2.65 inches this week.  Color.
15-20 mph from W.  62 degrees F.  60 degrees F end of pier. 25% cumulus. 0.6 inches rain.  Lake turning.  Color.
15-20 mph SE.  54 degrees F.  55 degrees F end of pier.  53 degrees bottom.  1.4 inches of rain.  Color still good.  10% clouds -cumulus and cirrus.
50 degrees.  Wind 0-5 mph SSE.  High cumulus 30%.  0.6" rain.  Most leaves down some color.  Lots of algae on top.
74 degrees F. 100% cloudy.  5-10 mph SSE.  Ice out 4/15.  About 8" rain in May (gauge not up).
72 degrees F. 10% clouds.  Loon nesting on island.  Heavy dragonfly hatch.  Mosquitoes + black flies gone.
20% cloudy. 10-15 mph W.  Lake highest since fall 1987. 8" rain since mid-June (18th) .
86 degrees F. Sunny. High cirrus. SSE 0-5 mph. 7/23 power out 12 hours. Trees down. 3/4" rain. Water 81 degrees F. No chicks.
64 degrees F. 5% cloudy. 0-5 mph WNW.  Lake level normal.
57 degrees F. SE wind. Gusty 5-15 mph. 5% cirrus. Great day for early Nov!  Skin of ice on 1/3 lake this A.M.  Lots of daphnea 12' to 3'.
SSE wind 5-15 mph. 58 degrees F.- 15% cirrus.  Lake up thanks to beavers.  Early spring then cold- back to normal.
65 degrees F.- S wind 5-10 mph.- 50% cumulus. Rain showers until 12:30. 1.3" rain since 6/12.
72 degrees F.- calm. 10% cirrus- 6/19-6/20- 2.1" rain with 1" in 30 minutes.  6/21-6/30- 1.25" rain. 7/1 - 3.5" rain.  A toad-strangling- gully washing deluge!!
78 degrees F- calm- high haze.  Only 1/2" rain in last 2/5 weeks.  27' sample had a slight sulfur smell.
76 degrees F.- W wind 5-10 mph.- 30% cumulus.  Cloudy and 100% overcast on 8/5 and 8/16.
60 degrees F- ENE wind at 10-15 mph- gusts to 20 mph. 5% clouds. Barometer 30.25- distinct sulfur smell at 27 feet.
45 degrees F- W wind 5-15 mph. 2% cirrus clouds. Barometer 30.18. 2.75" rain in last week.  12" snow 10/6.
Wind SSE 10-15 mph.  Barometer 29.99.  Temp 82 degrees F.
Wind NE 10-15 mph.  Barometer 29.99.  Temp 82 F.
Wind NW 10-15 mph.  Barometer 30.33.  Temp 61 degrees F.  No clouds - cold front.  80 F yesterday.
Wind WSW 0-5 mph.  Barometer 29.95.  Temp 72 degrees F.  5% clouds.
Wind ESE 5-10 mph.  Temp 88 degrees F.  High haze.  Humidity 95%+.
Wind SSE 0-5 mph.  Temp 50 F.  High cirrus 80%- but good light.
70F- barometric pressure: 30.05" Hg- 40% cumulus. Ice Out 4/18. High water- cold and wet since- 2 loon eggs on nest.  NW wind at 5-10 mph.
64F- barometric pressure: 29.95" Hg- 3% Cirro Cumulus- 0-5mph N- 1 Loon Chick! Mosquitoes bad.
78 F- Barometric pressure: 29.28" Hg- 5-10 mph SSE- 80% Cirrus- Very rainy- outlet beaver dam breached- and 2 baby loons.
64 F-  30.12" Hg- 100% high haze- Satellite flyover.
Temperature is 80 degrees F- 10-15 W mph wind- 50% strato cumulus clouds- loon chick is growing- no Eurasian water Milfoil at landing- and 1 baby loon growing.
80 F- 10-15 mph SSW wind- 2% Clouds- Satellite Flyover.  Great day!
70 F- 5-10 mph E wind-  50% Clouds- and Satellite Flyover.
5-10 mph S-  40% low Cirrus and Haze.  Rain yesterday p.m. and predicted this p.m..
Temperature is 40 degrees F- 10-15 NW mph wind- 5% cirrus clouds- Cold!  1 baby loon still on lake.  Turnover in progress.
Sunny/haze. 5-10 mph NE- 67 F. 30.09" Hg. Loon nest east side of our island.
Cumulus 30%- 0-5 mph W. 76 F. 30.02" Hg. Loon nest abandoned - no chicks.
2% Cirrus- 0-5mph W- 75 F- Beautiful day.  No one else

column1: on the lake.  Eight boats on July 4th.

column2: Cirrus 3%- 10-15 mph SE- beautiful day- color starting.
Clouds 30%. 0-5 WSW- 70 F. 6" snow 10/1. Gorgeous indian summer day.
High haze.  62 F.  ESE 5-10 mph- gusty.  Ice out 4/17.
High clouds- no wind.  Better secchi reading then 5/11
5% clouds- SW 5-10 mph.  Lots of rain
High cirrus clouds- NE 0-5 mph.  74 F.  30.08" Hg.  Young eagle soaring.  Lovely day.
20% puffy cumulus.  SSW 10-15 mph.  Gusty.  2 adult loons- no chick.  66 F.  30.01" Hg.  Daphnia at 24' depth.
20% strato cumulus.  74 F.  W 0-5 mph.  30.08" Hg.  Lake level lower.
10% cumulus.  NNE 10-15 mph.  62 F.  30.02" Hg.  Nice day after rainy- cool week.
50% cumulus- NNW 10-15 mph.  62 F.  30.21" Hg.  41 F last night -- brrr!  Summer
No clouds- S 0-5 mph- 70 F.  Beautiful day.  Sulphur odor 27'.
Boat landing unusable.  Very low water level.  72 F.  30.18" Hg.  40% cirro cumulus.  SW 0-5 mph.  Strong sulpher at 24' and 27'.
60% cirrus 20% cumulus.  NE 10-15 mph.  58 F.  30.02" Hg.  39 F last night.  Lake down about 1 foot.
Scattered cirrus and cumulus.  S 0-5 mph.  76 F.  30.05" Hg.  One of the best summer days so far!
Scattered clouds in west (front approaching).  78 F.  S 5-10 mph.  Lake about 11" low. Great day.
68 F- 30% cumulus- 0-5 mph NNE- 30.00' Hg- Ice out 3/11/05- Daphnea near shore- Loon nest on island- lots of snow/rain--first nice day early in week in May.
5% cirrus- 0-5mph S- 30.09" hg- No loon chicks- tried twice on island- not on nesting platform.
70F- High haze- 0-5mph S- 29.80" Hg- Lots of rain in June.
74 F- 60% thin cirrus- 5-10 mph S - gusty- 30.04" Hg- 5" rain last week
66F- 5%Strato Cumulus- 0-5 mph NNE- 29.90" Hg- Some color along shore- lake down about 12".
68F- 30% Cumulus- 0-5mph S- Great summer- but dry -- lake is low.
95% mixed clouds- Beautiful fall color- Lake still down- Loons are gone.
57.2 F- 30.00" Hg.  95% clouds.  Clearing.  Ice out 4/14/2006.  Trees budding early.  Need rain.
78 F.  29.97" Hg.  Winds 0-5 mph.  50% cirrus/cumulus.  Front moving in from west.
67 F.  30.15"  Hg.  0 wind.  15% scattered cumlus.  Lake very low for June - 9".
67 F- 30.00" Hg.  95% clouds.  Very dry.  Sprinkle this morning.  Lake down 9"+.  No loon chicks.
70 F.  29.94" Hg.  100% clouds.  Sprinkles.  Very dry.  0.86" all July.  Lake down 12"+.  1 loon chick 7/7/2006.
74 F.  30.09" Hg.  Winds 5-10 mph.  10% cumulus.  Lake down 10-12 ".  Loon chick doing well.
64F.  29.94" Hg.  65% clouds.  E 10-15 mph.  Leaves down already.  Ice out 12/1/2006.
63 degrees F 27% humidity windy (red flag warning) 30.21"hg
70 degrees F- 30.06 " Hg- high cirrus 10%- wind 15 - 20 mph with gusts to 30 mph- eagles soaring- loons on nest on island near deep hole- H2O 65.1 degrees F at 3'- what a day!
84 degrees F- scattered cumulus 15% WSW10-15 mph- hot and muggy with rain in forecast- no loons on nest.
63 degrees F- 83% Rel Humidity- windy 10-15 mph + gusts- 50% cumulus- loon not on nest
no clouds- gorgeous day- wind S 0-5 mph
85 degrees F- 29.71 " Hg- 70 5 rl humidity- winds WSW 0-5 mph- hot and sunny.
72 degress F- 30.21" Hg- bank of cirrus in west-20%- 5-15 mph SSW- no loon chicks

70 degrees F- 53% rel humidity-30.09 " Hg- few cumulus 5%- 10-15 mph +gusts- dry!- lake down at least 20 inches-  lowest ever seen by one who has been coming to the lake since 1943.  Rock piles showing for the first time.
72 degrees F- 30.11 " Hg- 43% rel humidity- 5% clouds WSW 0-5 mph- water down at least 24"- rocks popping up all over- boat landing unusable
48 degrees- 30.00" Hg- 52% RHum- NNE@5-10mph-20% cirrus Circled shoreline and checked landing area.  No unusual plants found.
67 degrees- 29.83" Hg- W@ 10-15mph- 40% cumulus.  Loons abandoned nest on our island.  Don't know if high water or predators.
71 degrees- 29.88" Hg- S 10-15mph- high haze- 30% clouds.  No loon chicks.  Nested on island again; ignored nesting platform again- so moved to a new location.
83 degrees- 29.87" Hg- NNW@5-10mph- 10% strato-cumulus- high haze
62 degrees- 30.09" Hg- NNW@ 5-10mph- clear- forecast patchy frost tonight- very little rain in August.
SSE wind 10-15 mph- ice out 4/23- loons back 4/25
WNW 10-15 mph- 72 degrees F- no loon chicks- 3 adults on lake.
Finally a warm day- SSW wind 0-5 mph- 81F- 30.09" Hg- Lake level down 9"
No wind- 2% cumulus on horizon- 68 degrees F- 30.12 " Hg- Lake still clear

Beautiful first day of fall- 65 degrees F- 30.24" Hg- no wind- 5% clouds- Lake level down 9" and only 0.05" rain so far this month!  Water very clear.  Another 9.50' secchi this year- the deepest ever for Annabelle.
47 degrees- wind N 5-10 mph- 30.05" Hg- No Clouds- 1 pair of loons
61 degrees- wind calm- 29.56" Hg- high cirrus 50%- front moving in
69 degrees- wind NW 5-10 mph- 29.88 " Hg- clear- 1/2" rain yesterday- water less brown than usual - nearly clear- loons nested on island near nesting platform.
73 degrees- wind W 5-10mph- 30.03" Hg- 30% cumulus- no loon chicks
76 degrees- wind NW 5-10 mph- 30.03" Hg- 10% cumulus- lake up 4" on guage
68 degrees- wind ESE 0-5 mph- overcast with spotty sun- 1 loon chick- lots of rain in June and July- now at 91% of normal for the most recent 12 months.  No DO data.

77.9 Degrees- wind NE 0-5 mph- 30.12" Hg- 10% cumulus+high haze- water level up 15-3/4" on gauge since spring- lots of rain- bogs full- some algae for first time (lasted for one or two days and gone-collected on the windward side of the lakeshore.)
58 degrees- wind WSW 0-5 mph- 30.30" Hg- clear- level down from highest- only one loon left on lake
55 F- 29.94" Hg- NNE 0-5mph- Clear- Ice out 04/26/11- lake level very high- Loons back.
75F-  30.12" HgS- SSE 5-15mph- 5% cloud- Level down 16cm since mid-May- no loon chicks.
81F- 30.09" Hg- W 0-5mph- Clear- 3 loons- 3 other boats on the lake at once!
72F- 30.15" Hg- NNW 10-15 mph- Cumulus 20%- Rain yesterday- Level up 5.1 cm- 3 adult loons- no chicks.
74F- 30.00" Hg- W 5-10mph- clear- unusually warm- no frost yet.
Was not here for ice out- and my fishing boat motor died- so this is my first report for the year taken with our new pontoon boat.    %5 clouds- 5mph SE wind- 30.09" Hg- no loon chicks this year.
50% clouds so had to wait for sun to take secchi reading- 0-5 mph SW- beautiful day.
30% clouds- 0-15mph SW- 30.02"Hg- 75?.  Very gusty winds.  Boat landing repair completed so 1 or 2 extra boats.
Wind NNE 10-15 mph- 5% cloud cover with high haze- no loon chicks.
Wind SSW 10-15 mph +gusts- 76+#8457;- 29.97" Hg- High Haze.
Wind SW 0-5 mph- 70+#8457;- 29.71" Hg- 10 % high cirrus-
Wind NW 5-10 mph- 61+#8457;- 30.09 " Hg- 3% cirrus on horizon- migrating baby loon 9/27.
SSE 0-5 mph- 30.30" Hg- high cirrus 5%- Loon nest Herzog Island- Ice out 5/9.
W 5-10 Gusty- 29.97" Hg- Cirrus 25%- no loon chick.
57+#8457;- 50% cumulus- 30.38" Hg.  Collected special water sample for satellite fly-over.
Four days after ice-out.  Clear-no clouds- 75+#8457;- 30.05" HG- Wind 0-5 mph SS.  Loons and mallards back.  Gorgeous day.
2% StratoCumulus- 5-10 mph NNE- 29.97" Hg- 76+#8457;.  Didn't see loons - on nest?  Water level up 7"!  Log in outlet?
15% Cumulus- 75+#8457;- 30.05 " Hg.  Two loon chicks! (Mike says it's a new pair on the lake. Heavy rain last evening.
60% StratoCumulus- 5-10 mph WNW- 70++#8457;.  Beautiful Day. Had to wait for clear spot in the clouds to take Secchi depth.
High haze- 5-10 mph S- 29.91" Hg- 79+#8457;.  Both Loon chicks doing fine.
5% Cirrus- 0-5 mph NNE- 30.40" Hg- 53+#8457;.  Water clearing - less phyllo and zoo plankton.
1% Cumulus. calm- 30.24" Hg- 55+#8457;.  Saw both loon chicks - parents gone.  Chicks last sighted on 11/9/15.
Ice out 4/16/16.  NNE @ 0-5mph.  60% strato-cumulus.  37+#8457;.  30.18" Hg.  Loons back.
NW5-15mph- 100% Cloud cover- so secchi taken on 7/2/16. NW5-15mph- 100% Cloud cover- so secchi taken on 7/2/16.  30.12" Hg.  57+#8457;.  Cold and misty day.  No loon chicks.

W 5-10 mph.  20%  strato-cumulus.  30.03" HG.  82+#8457;.  One loon chick hatched- one egg didn't.  On our island.  Second nesting-high water and heavy storms 7/11 and 7/21.  Broke the top out of one hemlock each time.  Second storm damaged Rigacki cottage- many trees down on west end of Musgorve's island- and half a dozen trees- including two large white pines on our island.  Never saw trees move like that before-twisting and bending. W 5-10 mph.  20%  strato-cumulus.  30.03" HG.  82+#8457;.  One loon chick hatched- one egg didn't.  On our island.  Second nesting-high water and heavy storms 7/11 and 7/21.  Broke the top out of one hemlock each time.  Second storm damaged Rigacki cottage- many trees down on west end of Musgorve's island- and half a dozen trees- including two large white pines on our island.  Never saw trees move like that before-twisting and bending.  2-4" of rain in each storm.
SSW 0-5 mph.  20% Strato-cumulus.  74+#8457;.  30.09" HG.  Loon chick growing.
SSE 0-5 mph.  64+#8457;.  30.30" Hg.  Loons still here feeding chick.
Couldn't do last two weeks in August.  SSE 0-5 with gusts.  Single loon chick growing.  Parents very protective.  Hope it makes it out this fall.
60% Stratocumulis- ESE 10-15mph- 76+#8457;. 29.99" Hg- Loons calling- but no chicks.  Very wet with high water.
65+#8457;- 29.59' Hg- W 10-15 mph with gust up to 22 mph- 60% Stratocumulus- No loon chicks- 4 Gooslings
72+#8457;- 29.77" Hg- W 0-5mph- 30% stratocumulus- No loon chicks.
66+#8457;- 30.03" Hg- W 10-15 mph- 5% Cumulus- Beautiful day!
78+#8457;- 29.99 " Hg- SW 10-15mph- High haze + 10% cumulus- No strange plants (AIS) observed.
Ice out 4/25- Loons back 4/25 among floating ice- 0 mph- no clouds
20% cirrus- 5-10 mph ESE- 30.0" Hg- No loon chicks
30.15"Hg- 71+#8457;- 30% cumulus- 5-10 mph NW- gusty 15+ mph- no loon chicks this year
Frost last night and tonight.  Cold Northwest wind.
